# iPad-First Design (MANDATORY)

## Viewport & Safari

- Always include: `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no">`
- Use CSS `dvh` units instead of `vh` (Safari dynamic toolbar)
- Set `touch-action: none` on the manipulative workspace
- Set `display: standalone` in PWA manifest for home-screen launch
- Test on actual iPad Safari — Chrome DevTools is not sufficient for final validation

## Touch Targets

- Fraction blocks: minimum 60×60 points
- Buttons: minimum 44×44 points (Apple HIG)
- No hover-dependent interactions — everything must work with tap/drag
- Single-touch model: track `isDragging` boolean, process first touch only, ignore subsequent touch points

## Gestures

- Use `@use-gesture/react` for drag-and-drop — never raw `onTouchStart`/`onTouchEnd`
- Disambiguate scroll vs. drag on the workspace
- 500ms debounce on Split button (matches animation duration)
- Queue max depth: 2 actions. Drop extras with a brief visual pulse.

## Performance Budgets

| Metric | Target |
|---|---|
| Initial load (LCP) | < 2 seconds |
| Time to interactive | < 3 seconds |
| JS bundle (gzipped) | < 150 KB |
| Animation framerate | 60 fps |
| Touch response latency | < 100ms |
| Memory (heap) | < 80 MB |
| Total asset size | < 500 KB |

Target device: 2020 iPad 8th gen (A12 chip, 3 GB RAM, iPadOS Safari).

## Animation Rules

- Only animate composited properties: `transform` and `opacity`
- NEVER animate `width`, `height`, `left`, `top` (triggers layout)
- Use `will-change: transform` on actively dragged blocks only — remove after gesture ends
- Split animation: 400ms, ease-out. Total width preserved.
- Combine animation: 350ms, ease-in-out. Combined width = sum of parts.

## Audio

- `AudioContext.resume()` must be called on user gesture (the "Start Lesson" button)
- Mute toggle always visible in header
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` media query (also mute sounds)
